Gauteng's health department is feeling the effects of the growing COVID-19 numbers. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - More than one million gravesites are being prepped in Pretoria as the province braces for an increase in COVID-19 deaths. Gauteng's health department is feeling the effects of the growing COVID-19 numbers. Gauteng Health MEC Bandile Masuku says the province has approximately 1.5-million burial sites that can be easily accessed should the need arise. READ: Gauteng Health MEC states COVID-19 strategy is focused As of Tuesday, the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in Gauteng is 71,488, with 21,414 recoveries and 478 deaths. #Covid_19SA Gauteng Government is preparing for the worst. This grave site on the outskirts of Pretoria, the country's capital is being prepared & reserved for Covid-19 burials. Gauteng is poised to become the #Covid_19SA epicentre soon. #eNCA pic.twitter.com/CLnEzAHbV5  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.